label: LABEL
definition: AL definition@en
specimen type: C 'has specified output' some (% and 'has role' some 'specimen role')

label: adult arthropod specimen collection process
definition: A live arthropod specimen collection process in which the arthropods are in the adult stage.

label: animal-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is biting an animal.

label: animal-biting outdoor arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An animal-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs outside a building.
parent class: animal-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

label: aquatic arthropod specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process that has the objective of collecting mosquitoes from an aquatic environment.

label: arthropod resting in animal house specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that catches specimens resting inside an animal house.

label: arthropod resting outdoors on artificial support specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod resting outdoors specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod rests on a processed material such as a wall or furniture.
parent class: arthropod resting outdoors specimen collection by aspiration

label: arthropod resting outdoors on natural support specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod resting outdoors specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod rests on an unprocessed material such as a plant.
parent class: arthropod resting outdoors specimen collection by aspiration

label: arthropod resting outdoors specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An animal-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is resting outside a building during a period of inactivity.
parent class: animal-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

label: arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: A live arthropod specimen collection process that involves the use of an aspirator, a device which draws an arthropod by suction into a container.

label: arthropod specimen collection process
definition: A specimen collection process that has the objective of collecting arthropods as specimens.

label: human-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is biting a human.

label: human-biting indoor arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is biting a human inside a building.
parent class: human-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

label: human-biting outdoor arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration designed to catch specimens that are in the process of biting a human outside a building.
parent class: human-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

label: knockdown arthropod specimen collection by pyrethrum spray
definition: A knockdown arthropod specimen collection process in which the pesticide is pyrethrum.

label: knockdown arthropod specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process that involves exposing arthropods to pesticide, then collecting them once they become dead or immobilized.

label: live arthropod specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process meant to collect live specimens.

label: egg specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process in which the arthropods are in the embryo stage.

label: larval specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process in which the arthropods are in the larval stage.

label: pupal specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process in which the arthropods are in the pupal stage.
